PLAYING — Tips and Strategy

ECONOMY BASICS
  - Food is produced by agribusiness ('a') sectors with high fert.
    Without food, civilians starve and productivity collapses.
  - Iron comes from iron mines ('m') with high min resource.
    Iron feeds LCM factories ('j') and HCM factories ('k').
  - LCM (light construction materials) is needed for building
    almost everything: ships, planes, land units, tech/research.
  - Gold dust from gold mines ('g') contributes to treasury income.
  - Oil from oil fields ('o') powers refineries and units.

TECH AND RESEARCH
  To advance your technology:
    1. Build research labs ('r') — feed them lcm, oil, dust
    2. Build tech centers ('t') — feed them lcm, oil, dust
    3. Build libraries ('l') — feed them lcm for education
  Higher tech unlocks better ships, planes, and units.

PRODUCTION PIPELINE EXAMPLE
  iron mine → (iron) → LCM factory → (lcm) → library → education
  iron mine → (iron) → HCM factory → (hcm) → harbor → ships
  gold mine → (dust) → capital treasury

DISTRIBUTION SYSTEM
  Set thresholds (info threshold) and distribution centers
  (info distribute).  The update moves commodities automatically
  so sectors stay stocked.  This is far more efficient than
  manual 'move' commands.

MILITARY PIPELINE
  1. des X,Y e               enlistment center
  2. (wait for >=60% eff)    auto-enlist runs each update
  3. demobilize X,Y 500      move sector mil to nat_reserve
  4. enlist target 100       deploy reserve to any sector
  5. attack                  assault enemies with military

COMMON MISTAKES
  - Forgetting to set food thresholds: civilians starve!
  - Exploring without food: new sectors run out quickly
  - Building harbors inland: ships require coastal sectors (coa=1)
  - Not setting distribution centers: goods pile up at source

